1.title: Durst Girls Gone Wild
1.plot: After refusing to do their chores and some very rebellious behavior from Kendra, the girls realize they've been too hard on Mom and decide to clean the house and make her dinner. Can four bickering sisters pull off such a task in time to surprise Mom?

2.title: Buffalo's Got Talent
2.plot: An opportunity to perform in a local talent show causes a rift amongst the girls, with drama queen Kendra refusing to cooperate. Sarah, wanting a closer relationship with their estranged father, invites Dad to the show. Will he be there to support them if they perform?

3.title: Mom Dot Com
3.plot: The girls are off to Sin City when a family friend invites the Durst quadruplets to sing the national anthem at a rodeo event in Las Vegas. For Mom back at home, that means a welcome relief from all the sibling squabbles and chaos--but for older brother Travis, it means a weekend of chaperoning four out-of-control sisters in the world's biggest playground!

4.title: Viva Las Vegas
4.plot: When the Durst quadruplets are invited to sing the national anthem at a rodeo event in Las Vegas, the girls are off to Sin City! For Mom back at home, that means a welcome relief from all the sibling fighting. For the girls, it means lots of sightseeing and a wild game of paintball.

5.title: Fashion Times Four
5.plot: As their senior year at high school approaches, the girls decide to tour North Dakota State University as a potential college choice. But any trip together for the girls means lots of fighting; from car space to vying for attention from cute boys!

6.title: Quadruplets on Ice
6.plot: With Travis' departure to college imminent, Mom decides to take the kids on one last snowboarding trip to the mountains for some family bonding. But for Travis, teaching his four beginner sisters how to navigate the slopes is not an easy task.

imdb.plot outline: This real-life series follows the lives of Calli, Kendra, Megan and Sarah -- 17-year-old, vivacious, hellacious identical auburn-haired quadruplets. Everyday joys and headaches assume four times the fun -- or pressure -- as the girls navigate their senior year of high school juggling boys, class work, jobs, gossip, sports, prom, and what lies ahead.
